article.description: Dirk Nowitzki found his shooting touch just in time to prevent the Mavericks from wasting all of their 20-point halftime lead.
article.headline: Walker sunk 22 points, grabbed 14 boards
article.linkText: Mavs hold off Bucks after losing big lead
article.story:
DALLAS (AP) -- Antoine Walker had 22 points and 14 rebounds, and Dirk Nowitzki made two key fourth-quarter 3-pointers to help the Dallas Mavericks withstand a late rally by the Milwaukee Bucks and win 101-92 Tuesday night. Steve Nash added 14 points and 12 assists, Antawn Jamison came off the bench to score 17, and Nowitzki had 20 points and 11 rebounds to help Dallas to its third straight win. The Mavericks improved to 14-2 at home. Michael Redd led the Bucks with 25 points while Desmond Mason added 18. Bucks rookie T.J. Ford, the former University of Texas star, went scoreless in 12 first-half minutes and finished with four points -- missing all five of his field-goal attempts. Ford did dish out 11 assists in his second NBA game in Texas. Milwaukee, which trailed by 20 points at halftime, closed to 93-90 with 2:07 left on a layup by Redd. But Nowitzki hit consecutive 3-pointers from the same spot on the right wing to push the lead to 99-90 with 1:21 to play, closing out the Bucks. The Mavericks ended the first half on a 22-7 run to take a 57-37 halftime lead. But Milwaukee opened the third quarter with an 11-2 run and got as close as 74-71 with 1:17 to go in the period on consecutive 3-pointers by Redd.

Game notes
Mavericks C Shawn Bradley was in uniform after missing the previous seven games due to back spasms. ... Dallas F Eduardo Najera missed his second straight game because of a sore left knee. ... Despite the loss, the Bucks have won 10 of the last 14 meetings with the Mavericks.
